{
  "answer": "**Manusmṛti 1.91** states that the sole duty assigned by the Lord to the Śūdra (Sudra) is to serve the other three *varṇas* (Brahmana, Kshatriya, and Vaiśya) without malice.[^1]\n\nThis verse follows the description of duties for the other *varṇas* (1.88–90) in the context of creation, where the four *varṇas* emanate from the body of the Self-existent One (1.31), with specific roles to maintain the world order.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Manu, *Manusmṛti*, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/01/translation/#p-26a572).\n\n[^2]: Manu, *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 1, [chapter](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/01/translation/).",
